{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 180°C and line 2 large baking trays with baking paper.","Place hazelnuts in mixing bowl and chop <b>4 sec\/speed 5<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place butter, light brown sugar and muscovado sugar in mixing bowl then mix <b>20 sec\/speed 4<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add flour, cocoa powder, egg, baking powder and salt then mix <b>20 sec\/speed 3<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add raisins, oats, chocolate chips and reserved chopped nuts then mix <b>30 sec\/\/speed 3<b>. Finish mixing by hand with spatula, if necessary.","Using wet hands, roll 2 tablespoons dough into balls then flatten each slightly. Place on prepared trays, spaced 5 cm apart. Bake for 15-18 minutes (180°C). Leave on trays for 5 minutes (they will be very soft) then transfer to wire racks to cool.","Serve or store in an airtight container for up to 5 days."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["100 g blanched hazelnuts","130 g unsalted butter, soft","120 g light brown sugar","50 g dark brown muscovado sugar","140 g plain flour","20 g cocoa powder","1 large egg","½ tsp baking powder","1 pinch fine sea salt","100 g raisins","70 g rolled oats","100 g dark chocolate chips"]}],"id":"r133748","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-qktpEc5xXug\/XZWp6592EeI\/AAAAAAAAfQo\/rj4HqqUxgksziX-lUEN8wk-OsUUuaUW1QCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_8FXR4MuFvVZaVPii.png","title":"Chocolate, Raisin and Hazelnut Biscuits","publishedAt":"2017-11-24T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"4.6 g","fat":"18.2 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"26.9 g","calories":"1211 kJ \/ 290 kcal"},"usefulItems":"2 baking trays and baking paper, wire racks, oven","basicInfo":["easy","10m","35m","16 pieces"]}